In February, there are 28 days. Suzanne walks every third day, so in February there are 28/3 = 9 full cycles of her walking schedule. This means she walks 4 miles x 9 = 36 miles in total in February.

However, since she walks every third day, the last day of February may not always fall on a walking day. If February ends on a non-walking day for Suzanne, then she will not walk on that day. Therefore, the fewest number of miles she can walk in February is 36 miles if February ends on a walking day for Suzanne.

\boxed{36}

